+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012W89MN5bF8rLM62EpokrUp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me compile a comprehensive overview for you:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Overview\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── types.ts      (Core type definitions)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts     (Build engine implementation)\n│   │   ├── templates.ts  (Template factory functions)\n│   │   └── index.ts      (Public exports)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep      (Empty - all plugins need to be created)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts      (Core engine tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Core Type Definitions (src/core/types.ts)\n\n```typescript\n// SiteConfig - Main configuration for the static site generator\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\n// ContentFile - Represents a single content page/post\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;                      // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;                        // optional publication date\n  tags?: string[];                      // optional tag list\n  template?: string;                    // optional template name\n}\n\n// BuildContext - Shared context passed through the entire build\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];                 // current files being processed\n  output: Map<string, string>;          // output path -> rendered HTML\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;          // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;           // shared plugin data store\n}\n\n// PluginHooks - Lifecycle hooks that plugins can implement\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\n// Plugin - Plugin interface that all plugins must conform to\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];               // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\n// Template - Template for rendering content\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Build Engine (src/core/engine.ts)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Plugin registration and management\n- Template registration and retrieval\n- **Topological sorting** for plugin dependency resolution\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Sequential build pipeline with three stages:\n  1. **beforeBuild** hooks\n  2. **transformContent** hooks (applied to each file in plugin order)\n  3. Template rendering\n  4. **afterBuild** hooks\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)` - Register a plugin\n- `registerTemplate(template: Template)` - Register a template\n- `resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]` - Get plugins in dependency order (throws on circular/missing dependencies)\n- `async build(files: ContentFile[]): BuildContext` - Execute the full build pipeline\n- `getPlugins(): Plugin[]` - Get all registered plugins\n- `getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>` - Get all registered templates\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- Files array is cloned at start of build\n- Each file gets an HTML output based on its slug (e.g., `test-post.html`)\n- Falls back to raw content if no matching template exists\n- All plugin hooks execute in dependency order\n\n---\n\n### 4. Templates (src/core/templates.ts)\n\n**createDefaultTemplate():**\n- Name: `'default'`\n- Wraps content in proper HTML structure with:\n  - Doctype, meta charset, title (combines article title + site title)\n  - Optional `<time>` element if date is provided\n  - Content wrapped in `<article><div class=\"content\">`\n\n**createListTemplate():**\n- Name: `'list'`\n- Similar structure but wraps content in `<div class=\"list\">` instead of article\n\n---\n\n### 5. Core Tests (tests/core.test.ts)\n\n14 test cases covering:\n- Plugin registration and retrieval\n- Template registration and retrieval\n- Default template rendering with variables (title, site title, date)\n- List template rendering\n- Raw content fallback when no template\n- Plugin hook execution (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Plugin dependency resolution order\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugins transforming content in order\n- Shared data store functionality\n- Metadata preservation (author, category, tags, dates)\n- Empty file list handling\n\n---\n\n### 6. Plugin Tests & Specifications\n\n#### **6.1 RSS Feed Plugin** (tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createRssFeedPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML in `feed.xml` (afterBuild hook)\n- Feed items contain HTML content in CDATA sections\n- Items include category tags from `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` (Map<string, ContentFile[]>)\n- Channel title from config\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates gracefully\n- Links use baseUrl from config for both channel link and item links\n- Format: `https://example.com/post-slug.html`\n\n#### **6.2 Markdown Extension Plugin** (tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Converts markdown to HTML using `marked` library (transformContent hook)\n- **Footnotes support** with `[^1]` syntax:\n  - Renders as `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n  - Renders footnotes section at bottom with `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n  - Each footnote wrapped in `<li id=\"fn-N\">` \n- **Admonition/container blocks** with `:::type` syntax:\n  - `:::note` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n  - `:::warning` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`\n  - `:::tip` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`\n- Preserves existing HTML in content\n- Handles empty content gracefully\n\n#### **6.3 Syntax Highlighting Plugin** (tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Adds `highlighted` class to code blocks with language (transformContent hook)\n- Extracts language from `class=\"language-*\"` on `<code>` tag\n- Adds `data-language=\"*\"` attribute to corresponding `<pre>` tag\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Ignores plain code blocks without language class\n- Does NOT modify inline `<code>` tags (only `<pre><code>` blocks)\n- Preserves code block content\n\n#### **6.4 Asset Pipeline Plugin** (tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Rewrites relative asset URLs to `/assets/` path (transformContent hook)\n- For `<img src=\"./image.png\"` → `<img src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n- For `<a href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `<a href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n- Leaves absolute URLs (http/https) unchanged\n- Creates `asset-manifest` in `ctx.data` with structure: `{ assets: string[] }`\n- Accumulates manifest across multiple files\n- Does NOT double-process already-rewritten URLs (checks for `/assets/` prefix)\n- Handles files with no asset references\n\n#### **6.5 Taxonomy Plugin** (tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createTaxonomyPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Builds tag index in beforeBuild hook\n- Stores in `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` as `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n- **Case-normalizes tags to lowercase** (JavaScript/JAVASCRIPT → javascript)\n- Generates tag listing pages in afterBuild hook (format: `tags/tagname.html`)\n- Tag pages contain all posts with that tag by title\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles empty file list\n- Maps are persisted in ctx.data for other plugins (like RSS feed) to use\n\n#### **6.6 Search Index Plugin** (tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createSearchIndexPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Generates `search-index.json` in afterBuild hook\n- Index structure: Array of objects with:\n  - `slug`: string\n  - `title`: string\n  - `content`: string (HTML tags stripped, plain text only)\n  - `tags`: string[] (optional, if present on file)\n- HTML tags completely removed from content\n- Code block content is included in searchable text\n- Valid JSON output\n- Handles empty file list (returns empty array)\n\n#### **6.7 Sitemap Plugin** (tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createSitemapPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in afterBuild hook\n- Valid XML 2.0 structure with `<?xml version=\"1.0\">`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` elements\n- Includes all HTML files from `ctx.output` keys\n- Includes tag page URLs from `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` (if present)\n- Includes `feed.xml` URL if it exists in output\n- URLs use baseUrl from config\n- Example URL format: `https://example.com/post-1.html`\n\n#### **6.8 Dev Server Plugin** (tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts)\n\nExpected plugin factory: `createDevServerPlugin()`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Stores dev server configuration in `ctx.data.get('dev-server-config')` in afterBuild hook\n- Config structure: `{ port: number; routes: Array<{path, handler}>; assetPaths: string[]; searchIndexPath: string }`\n- Default port: `3000`\n- Includes asset routes from `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` if available (handler: `'asset'`)\n- Includes static content routes from `ctx.output` keys (handler: `'static'`)\n- Includes search index path: `/search-index.json`\n- Gracefully handles missing asset-pipeline data (returns empty assetPaths)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Package.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Existing Plugin Files in src/plugins/\n\n**Status:** Empty directory (only `.gitkeep` exists)\n\nAll 8 plugins need to be created:\n1. `rss-feed.ts`\n2. `markdown-ext.ts`\n3. `syntax-highlight.ts`\n4. `asset-pipeline.ts`\n5. `sitemap.ts`\n6. `taxonomy.ts`\n7. `search-index.ts`\n8. `dev-server.ts`\n\n---\n\n### 9. Key Implementation Notes\n\n**Plugin Dependency Model:**\n- Plugins declare dependencies by name in the `dependencies` array\n- The engine uses topological sort (DFS) to determine execution order\n- Circular dependencies throw: `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"`\n- Missing dependencies throw: `\"{name} requires {dep}\"`\n\n**Plugin Hook Execution Order:**\n1. All plugins' `beforeBuild` hooks (in dependency order)\n2. All plugins' `transformContent` hooks (each plugin processes ALL files in order, file list is mutated)\n3. Template rendering for each file\n4. All plugins' `afterBuild` hooks (in dependency order)\n\n**Data Flow:**\n- Plugins can share data via `ctx.data` Map\n- Key conventions:\n  - `'taxonomy-tags'` → `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` (from taxonomy plugin)\n  - `'asset-manifest'` → `{ assets: string[] }` (from asset-pipeline plugin)\n  - `'dev-server-config'` → complex config object (from dev-server plugin)\n\n**HTML Content Handling:**\n- Content can be markdown or HTML or plain text\n- Markdown plugin converts markdown to HTML\n- Content is rendered into templates which wrap it in HTML structure\n- Some plugins work with HTML (syntax-highlight, asset-pipeline)\n\n---\n\nThis is a comprehensive static site generator framework with a DAG-based plugin system where plugins can depend on each other and pass data through a shared context."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a05fdb1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36143\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 44860</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a20e6a81-dc1f-4ef6-ada5-a034e35f5369","uuid":"1d32ac7d-112f-48e6-8f93-15066424e046","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace and give me a thorough overview of:\n1. Directory structure\n2. Content of src/core/ files (types, build engine, templates)\n3. Content of tests/core.test.ts\n4. Content of all test files in tests/plugins/\n5. package.json contents\n6. Any existing plugin files in src/plugins/\n\nBe very thorough - I need to understand exactly what interfaces/types are defined, what the tests expect, and what already exists.","agentId":"a05fdb1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me compile a comprehensive overview for you:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Overview\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── types.ts      (Core type definitions)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts     (Build engine implementation)\n│   │   ├── templates.ts  (Template factory functions)\n│   │   └── index.ts      (Public exports)\n│   └── plugins/\n│ 